1. Update raspberry PI repository

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade

2. Install python3-dev y python3-pip to interat with the sensor

sudo apt-get install python3-dev python3-pip

3. Update setuptools

sudo python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel

4. Install the Adafruit libraries

sudo pip3 install Adafruit_DHT
pip3 install adafruit-circuitpython-dht
sudo apt-get install libgpiod2

5. Install requests for REST API communication

pip install requests

5. Run the python3 command to execute the code

python3 dht_simpletest.py

## Reference:
https://learn.adafruit.com/dht-humidity-sensing-on-raspberry-pi-with-gdocs-logging/python-setup
